## 4. Hard Links vs. Soft Links vs. File Copy

| Feature                 | Hard Link              | Soft Link (Symlink)       | File Copy              |
|-------------------------|------------------------|---------------------------|------------------------|
| **Creates new inode?**  | No                     | Yes (new inode for link)  | Yes (new inode + data) |
| **Copies data blocks?** | No                     | No                        | Yes                    |
| **Disk space**          | ~0 (metadata only)     | ~few bytes (path string)  | Full duplicate         |
| **Time complexity**     | O(1)                   | O(1)                      | O(file size)           |
| **Cross-filesystem?**   | No                     | Yes                       | Yes                    |
| **Survives target deletion?** | Yes (independent) | No (becomes dangling)     | Yes (independent)      |
| **Modification visible to other?** | Yes (shared data) | Yes (same target)    | No (independent copy)  |
| **Java API**            | `Files.createLink()`   | `Files.createSymbolicLink()` | `Files.copy()`      |
| **For 19 GB, 10 copies**| ~346 ms, 0 GB extra   | ~instant, 0 GB extra      | ~621 sec, 190 GB extra |

