## 8. Benchmark Evidence

The following results from this project's benchmarks demonstrate the hard link
advantage on real Lucene indexes.

### 8.1 Large Index (10M docs, ~19 GB, 100 fields, 10 splits)

```
  +-------------------------------------------------+
  |                 | Copy+Delete | HardLink+Delete  |
  +-------------------------------------------------+
  | Total Time      |  1,999,016 ms |  1,361,625 ms  |
  | Copy/Link Phase |    621,546 ms |        346 ms  |
  | Delete Phase    |  1,377,470 ms |  1,361,279 ms  |
  +-------------------------------------------------+

  Copy/Link Phase Speedup: 1,796x faster
  Overall Speedup:         1.47x faster
  Time Saved:              ~10.6 minutes
```

### 8.2 Small Index (100K docs, ~421 MB, 50 fields, 10 splits)

```
  +-------------------------------------------------+
  |                 | Copy+Delete | HardLink+Delete  |
  +-------------------------------------------------+
  | Total Time      |     48,758 ms |     40,412 ms  |
  | Copy/Link Phase |      5,703 ms |          3 ms  |
  | Delete Phase    |     43,055 ms |     40,409 ms  |
  +-------------------------------------------------+

  Copy/Link Phase Speedup: 1,901x faster
  Overall Speedup:         1.21x faster
```

### 8.3 Key Observations

1. **The hard link phase is consistently ~1,800x faster** than file copying —
   346 ms vs. 621,546 ms for 19 GB
2. **The delete phase is identical** in both approaches because the same Lucene
   operations (term deletion + force merge) are performed
3. **The overall speedup grows with index size** because the copy phase scales
   linearly with data volume while the link phase scales with file count
4. **Peak disk usage drops dramatically**: 209 GB (copy) vs. 19 GB (hard link)
   before force-merge begins

### 8.4 Projected Savings at Scale

| Index Size | Copy Phase  | Link Phase | Copy Phase Savings | Peak Disk Savings |
|------------|-------------|------------|--------------------|-------------------|
| 421 MB     | 5.7 sec     | 3 ms       | ~5.7 seconds       | ~4.2 GB           |
| 19 GB      | 10.4 min    | 346 ms     | ~10.3 minutes      | ~190 GB           |
| 40 GB      | ~22 min*    | ~700 ms*   | ~22 minutes        | ~400 GB           |
| 100 GB     | ~55 min*    | ~1.5 sec*  | ~55 minutes        | ~1 TB             |

*Projected values based on linear scaling of observed benchmarks.

